      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Alan Kay contends that when normal people start creating and sending each other simulations as a way to exchange ideas, a new revolution will happen, similar to the one which the printing press eventually led to.  People will be able to exchange more interesting ideas, and will be able to have deeper conversations than they could before.",
      "id": "4532032b865c5fe3503d2f6332f07d6f"
